            <abstract>
                <p>In Ethiopian homiliaries the translation of Jacob of Sarug's Homily on the Annunciation was divided into three parts to cover three liturgical occasions i. e. the first three Sundays of Advent.  They concern: the Annunciation (for 
                    the first Sunday, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1633Homily"></ref>), the visit of Mary to Elizabeth (for the second Sunday , <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1683Homily"></ref>) and the vision of Joseph (for the third Sunday,
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1666Homily"></ref>).</p>
            </abstract>
